news.title: Private equity investments in Indian real estate rise 59% to $6.7 billion in 2025: Savills India
news.para: Private equity investment in Indian real estate saw a significant jump in 2025, reaching $6.7 billion. Foreign investors led the capital deployment, showing sustained interest. The office sector attracted the most investment, followed by data centres and residential properties.

news.title: CapitaLand India Trust to divest 20.2% stake in three data centres for ₹702 crore
news.para: CapitaLand India Trust has chosen to sell a segment of its interest in three developing data centres. This enables the trust to channel resources into new ventures. The acquisition is being made by an emerging data centre fund.

news.title: Gurugram civic body seals seven properties over ₹1.8 crore tax dues
news.para: Municipal Corporation of Gurugram sealed seven properties, recovering Rs 1.8 crore in overdue property taxes. This action, part of a broader campaign, aims to fund essential civic amenities. Officials emphasized that strict measures will persist against defaulters, urging prompt tax payments to avoid penalties.

news.title: Lucknow development body razes 12 illegal sites in Gudamba and Kakori
news.para: Lucknow Development Authority (LDA) demolished 12 construction sites across 43.75 acres in illegal colonies in Gudamba and Kakori. Enforcement teams targeted boundary walls and site offices in Kapasi village, Gudamba, and eight plots in Jaliyamau, Kathingra, Fatehganj, and Nathora villages, Kakori. The LDA continues its crackdown on unauthorized development.

news.title: KMC can repair unsafe buildings caught in civil dispute: Calcutta HC
news.para: The Calcutta High Court ruled that civil disputes cannot halt the renovation of a dilapidated building declared unsafe by KMC. The court emphasized the substantial risk to residents and the public, directing owners and a petitioner to jointly apply for a sanction plan for renovation within a fortnight.

news.title: Retail leasing to hit nine million sq ft in 2025 on mall-led recovery: Cushman & Wakefield
news.para: India’s retail real estate market is set to record its highest post-pandemic leasing at about nine million sq ft in 2025, driven by a strong year-end surge as new Grade A mall supply becomes operational. Improved availability of quality space has unlocked pent-up demand, while a robust supply pipeline is expected to push retail leasing further in 2026.

news.title: Yasmin Karachiwala buys two apartments worth ₹37.5 crore in Bandra West, Mumbai
news.para: Fitness trainer Yasmin Karachiwala has purchased two luxury ocean-facing apartments in Bandra West. The properties are valued at Rs 37.5 crore. Karachiwala, who trains Bollywood stars, invested in the elite Superstar-Signature Edition project. She also encouraged her niece to buy a flat in the same development. The project offers advanced wellness amenities.

news.title: Same apartment, multiple sale agreements shocks buyers in Bengaluru
news.para: Homebuyers are facing distress as builders repeatedly sell identical flats, exposing regulatory loopholes and alleged corruption in sub-registrar offices. Financial institutions are also failing to conduct mandatory due diligence. Despite discrepancies in carpet area, sub-registrar offices are registering multiple sale agreements for the same property, leaving innocent buyers defrauded.

news.title: Mumbai: Court orders eviction of trespassers from NRI businessman apartment after 15 year legal battle
news.para: A 15-year legal battle concluded with the Bombay City Civil Court ordering the eviction of trespassers from an NRI businessman's Dahisar apartment. The court ruled that the developers illegally resold the property after transferring title to the original buyer, Suresh Basantani, who had been working abroad.

news.title: NBCC sells 417 Amrapali Aspire housing units via e-auction for ₹1,045 crore
news.para: NBCC India has accomplished a successful e-auction, selling 417 residential units across Noida and Greater Noida West, generating ₹1,045 crore. These properties, originally part of the halted Amrapali Group projects, are being revitalized under Supreme Court mandates.

news.title: Himachal Pradesh cabinet approves township near Chandigarh
news.para: The Himachal Pradesh Cabinet has approved a world-class township near Chandigarh. The state will also implement a disaster risk reduction project. Amendments to real estate rules and land preservation acts were also approved.

news.title: Bagmane Prime Office REIT files draft papers for ₹4,000 crore IPO
news.para: Bagmane Prime Office REIT is set to embark on an Initial Public Offering aiming to raise as much as ₹4,000 crore. The proceeds will be directed towards acquiring prime office assets and investing in a stake of another burgeoning business park.

news.title: An avoidable crisis: Is India’s affordable housing segment facing an IndiGo-style fiasco?
news.para: The affordable housing market in India faces a serious challenge as developers pivot towards upscale projects, creating a void in accessible housing options for the masses. This situation echoes the difficulties faced by IndiGo in its earlier operational phases.

news.title: Gujarat to set up Indian AI Research Organisation at GIFT City
news.para: Gujarat Chief Minister Bhupendra Patel has approved the Indian AI Research Organisation. This facility will be established through a partnership between the state and central governments, and the Indian Pharmaceutical Alliance. The IAIRO aims to strengthen AI research and development.

news.title: Trichy corporation blacklists two contractors over smart city delays
news.para: Trichy Corporation has blacklisted two private contractors and imposed penalties totaling ₹1.8 crore for significant delays in Smart City Mission projects, including the Puthur AC mall and Marakkadai commercial complex. The corporation aims to recover losses and operationalize stalled facilities, while also cancelling an agreement for a multi-level car parking facility and exploring new operational models.

news.title: Blackstone-backed Horizon Industrial Parks files DRHP for ₹2,600-crore IPO
news.para: Horizon Industrial Parks, with the financial muscle of Blackstone, is gearing up to enter the public market with an Initial Public Offering aimed at raising around ₹2,600 crore. This momentum follows a successful pre-IPO raising of nearly ₹1,650 crore.

news.title: Office vacancy levels likely to hit historic lows by FY27 as demand outpaces supply: ICRA
news.para: India's office landscape is on the brink of a transformation. By FY2027, vacancy rates are anticipated to plunge to their lowest levels in several years. The demand for leasing is outpacing new developments, fueled by the rise of global capability centers, flexible workspace providers, and the booming BFSI industry.

news.title: India’s office leasing crosses 70 million sq ft in 2025: Colliers
news.para: India's office market saw record leasing in 2025, surpassing 70 million sq ft. Bengaluru led demand, with strong contributions from Delhi NCR and Hyderabad.  New office supply increased, but demand outpaced it, leading to lower vacancy and higher rentals.

news.title: InvITs, REITs distributions jump over 55% year-on-year in Q2 FY26: ICRA
news.para: Indian Infrastructure Investment Trusts and Real Estate Investment Trusts saw significant distribution growth in the second quarter of fiscal year 2026. This surge was driven by robust performance in sectors like roads, power, commercial real estate, and logistics.

news.title: REIT market in India crosses ₹2.3 lakh crore in asset value
news.para: India’s REIT market has grown into a mainstream asset class, with asset value of about ₹2.3 lakh crore and market capitalisation of nearly ₹1.66 lakh crore, surpassing Hong Kong. Supported by high occupancies, stable yields and strong returns, the sector is set for further growth as Sebi’s equity reclassification from 2026 is expected to broaden investor participation.
